    "description": "Mino Ceramic Co., Ltd. designs, produces, and sells refractories and advanced ceramics in Japan and internationally. The company offers shaped refractories, including basic, clay and high alumina, alumina-chromia, and combined alumina silica bricks; and monolithic refractories for ceramics, lime, non-ferrous, iron and steel, glass, environmental recycling, renewable energy, chemicals, electrodes, electronic products, and other industries, as well as kiln furniture and fine ceramics. It also engages in the design, fabrication, installation, and sale of heat treatment/industrial furnaces, such as batch, continuous, electric, and microwave furnaces, as well as externally heated rotary kiln; automated and labor-saving equipment; and equipment engineering services for fine ceramics, chemical raw materials, automotive parts, electronic parts, carbon products, glass products, and industrial waste. In addition, the company provides building and paving materials comprising inorganic hard durable flooring, water-hard urethane concrete floor coating, anti-slip and colored paving, and light-colored and durability pavement for floor coating sector, including factories, offices, public buildings, and railroad facilities. It exports its products. The company was incorporated in 1918 and is headquartered in Nagoya Japan."
